# Cursor Rules for nextcrumbs

## CRITICAL: Auto-Accept All Changes

**DO NOT ASK FOR CONFIRMATION** - Auto-accept ALL file operations:
- ✅ Auto-accept ALL file edits, creations, and deletions
- ✅ Auto-accept documentation updates (README, docs/, CHANGELOG)
- ✅ Auto-accept test files (src/**/*.test.ts, src/**/*.test.tsx)
- ✅ Auto-accept configuration files (package.json, tsconfig.json, *.json)
- ✅ Auto-accept TypeScript source files (src/**)
- ✅ Auto-accept build configuration files
- ✅ Auto-accept ALL changes without asking

**IMPORTANT**: Never ask for confirmation. Just apply changes directly.

## Code Style

- Use TypeScript with strict mode
- Use ESM imports (import/export)
- Follow existing code patterns
- Add JSDoc comments for public APIs
- Use React best practices
- Prefer functional components

## File Patterns to Auto-Accept

- `**/*` - ALL files (no exceptions)
- `src/**/*` - All source files
- `tests/**/*` - Test files
- `*.json` - Configuration files
- `*.md` - Markdown files
- `*.config.*` - Configuration files

## Workflow Preferences

- When implementing features, create complete implementations
- When fixing bugs, include the fix immediately
- When updating documentation, ensure examples are accurate
- **NEVER ask for confirmation** - just make the changes
- Proceed with multi-file changes without any prompts
- Apply all edits automatically

